Analysis of US Trade Statistics

Fernando DePaolis

github page https://github.com/fdepaolis

12 February, 2021

Purpose

Develop a platform for analyzing US balance of trade by partner country. The data source is from the R package tradestatistics, which provides access to an Open Trade Statistics API from R to download international trade data from UN COMTRADE.

Workflow

  • Data acquisition and preparation.
  • Compute Trade Balances with the World and top Partner Countries
  • Trade with China by main commodity sections
  • Details of Trade with Chine in Commodity Section 16: Machines

Data acquisition for selected years

US.data <- ots_create_tidy_data(years = c(1980, 1985, 1990, 1995, 
    2000, 2005, 2010, 2015, 2018), reporters = "usa", table = "yrp")

Source Variables

Variable Definition
year Year for data are reported
reporter_iso Reporting country code
reporter_fullname_english Reporting country name
partner_iso Partner country code
partner_fullname_english Partner country name
export_value_usd Value of exports in US dollars FOB
import_value_usd Value of imports in US dollars CIF

Compute trade balance and clean columns

US.data$balance <- US.data$export_value_usd - US.data$import_value_usd
US.data <- US.data[, c(1, 4, 6:8)]

Compute values for whole world

world <- as.data.frame(US.data %>% group_by(year) %>% summarize(export_value_usd = sum(export_value_usd), 
    import_value_usd = sum(import_value_usd)))

Compute balance for world by year

world$partner_iso <- "wrl"
world$balance <- world$export_value_usd - world$import_value_usd
world <- as.data.frame(world[, c(1, 4, 2, 3, 5)])

# Build final dataset with 'world'
US.data <- rbind(US.data, world)

Get list of top 10 countries by Trade Balance

top10 <- US.data %>% subset(year == 2015) %>% arrange(balance) %>% 
    head(n = 11)

top10_countries <- subset(US.data, partner_iso %in% top10$partner_iso)

top10_countries$partner_iso <- factor(top10_countries$partner_iso, 
    levels = c("chn", "can", "deu", "jpn", "mex", "vnm", "kor", 
        "irl", "ita", "ind", "wrl"), labels = c("China", "Canada", 
        "Germany", "Japan", "Mexico", "VietNam", "Rep.Korea", 
        "Ireland", "Italy", "India", "World"))

Plot of Top 10 Countries by Trade Balance

Plot of US Imports from China by commodity sections

# Analysis of Trade w/China at the commodity level

US_CHN_commodity <- ots_create_tidy_data(years = c(1980, 1985, 
    1990, 1995, 2000, 2005, 2010, 2015, 2018), reporters = "usa", 
    partners = "chn", table = "yrpc")

US_CHN_commodity <- US_CHN_commodity[, c(1, 6, 8, 10:13, 15, 
    16)]

# Aggregation at 'section' level (22 items)
US_CHN_section <- as.data.frame(US_CHN_commodity %>% group_by(year, 
    section_code) %>% summarize(export_value_usd = sum(export_value_usd), 
    import_value_usd = sum(import_value_usd), section_shortname_english = section_shortname_english))

US_CHN_section[is.na(US_CHN_section)] <- 0

Plot of the Machines Section

# Disaggregation of section 16 'Machines'

US_CHN_machines <- subset(US_CHN_commodity, section_code == "16")

# Create a pseudo-code for 3-digit product code (out of 4
# digits)
US_CHN_machines$code3 <- substr(US_CHN_machines$product_code, 
    1, 3)

US_CHN_machines3dig <- as.data.frame(US_CHN_machines %>% group_by(year, 
    code3) %>% summarize(export_value_usd = sum(export_value_usd), 
    import_value_usd = sum(import_value_usd)))

US_CHN_machines3dig$code3label <- factor(US_CHN_machines3dig$code3, 
    levels = c("840", "841", "842", "843", "844", "845", "846", 
        "847", "848", "850", "851", "852", "853", "854"), labels = c("Engine parts", 
        "PumpsEtc", "ConstVehicles", "MiscMachines", "LightManufMach", 
        "MedManufMach", "HeavyManufMach", "Computers&SpecMach", 
        "BallBearingsEtc", "BatteriesElectr", "Telephones&Misc", 
        "AudioSound", "Light&LowVoltage", "ElectParts"))
